==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[δακρυοαιμορρεειν]] (''dakryohaimorrheein'') to flow tears of blood: ''dakryo-'', "tear" + ''haima'', "blood" + ''rheein'', "to flow".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌdak´re-o-hem´o-re´ə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dacryohemorrhea}}

# {{symptom}} The discharge of tears mixed with blood; a hemorrhagic discharge from the lacrimal sac. 

*2. Bloody tears; bleeding from the tear ducts while crying; crying blood

